        [
          "Disgraced True Sabbat elder who lost his position and standing, and is responsible for seeing his pack claim True Sabbat status as his Act of Contrition"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Embraced in the early 1700s, you adjusted quickly to the power and prestige expected of a Lasombra.  Your pack fought with your intelligence and had several noteworthy victories against the sect's enemies by sneaking in and creating an army under their noses.  In the 1980s, your pack got in a little too far over their heads and the survivors spent the next 30 years in torpor. When you awoke, the military targets had shifted, but the goals were the same.  You assumed that your strategy of 300 years would be perfectly effective without realizing how much technology had changed in the intervening years.  Your shovel party was recorded by some random kine with their cell phones.  Your punishment for catching the attention of the Inquisition was the break up of your (surviving) pack, and your Rite of Contrition is to shape some of the surviving shovel heads into a proper pack.  Until you can educate one of them, you must also act as pack priest, despite lacking the status.  Rowe is your childe, but you prefer not to acknowledge that fact."
